==English==
===Etymology===
First attested circa [[w:17th century|17th century]], from {{L.}} [[obstreperus]] "[[clamorous]], [[noisy]]," from [[obstrepere]], "to make a noise against, oppose noisily," from [[ob-]], "[[against]]" + [[strepere]], "to [[noise]]."

